{"TopicId":192900,"ForumId":51,"TopicTitle":"500 kg \u0026quot;Jetpack\u0026quot;-ride around Kerbin in 7 hours","CreatedByName":"xendelaar","CreatedById":139535,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-03T21:48:28Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"xendelaar","CreatedById":139535,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-03T21:48:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-gb\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-gb\u0022\u003EI\u2019ve flown across many planets in the Kerbol system during the last 3k hours I wasted on this game\u2026 yet\u2026 I\u2019ve never payed any attention to the planet where it all began! KERBIN!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-gb\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-gb\u0022\u003ESo that\u2019s why I decided to circumnavigate Kerbin for a change :D. To make things a bit more interesting, I was wondering if i would be able to do it with a tiny light weight \u201CJetpack\u201D!\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI\u2019ve been playing around a bit and came up with this design. It\u2019s more of a tiny helicopter then a jetpack to be honest. But it\u2019s nice and compact! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-gb\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-gb\u0022\u003EHere are the key features of the design:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-gb\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-gb\u0022\u003EWeight: 480 kg (inlcuding lard ass Jeb)\u003Cbr\u003E\nTop speed: 175 m/s\u003Cbr\u003E\nMax Flying distance: infinite\u003Cbr\u003E\nPower consumption: 0.4 u/s\u003Cbr\u003E\nPower source: one huge \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003ERTG\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI made a small video (3:00) of Jeb using it to fly around the globe. I flew 4.000 km in 7 hours or so. And with Mechjeb as a flight assisstent, things were pretty manageable !\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-gb\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-gb\u0022\u003EHope you boys and girls like it. \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/Fxdyrkl1AVQ?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-04-06T22:36:28Z\u0022 title=\u002204/06/2020 10:36  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EApril 6, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by xendelaar\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EWords are hard\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-04T18:13:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat could be safer than flying around with a nuclear reactor on your back?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidCosmos","CreatedById":192336,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-04T18:46:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow! That was awesome! Could you please post the craft file? I love this thing!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"xendelaar","CreatedById":139535,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-06T22:38:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223766263\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192900\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221586024020\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002227914\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vanamonde\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/4/2020 at 8:13 PM, Vanamonde said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat could be safer than flying around with a nuclear reactor on your back?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaha no kerbals were harmed during the making of this video.\u00A0 Only a lawn chair died\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"xendelaar","CreatedById":139535,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-06T22:49:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223766270\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192900\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221586025997\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022192336\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidCosmos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/4/2020 at 8:46 PM, VoidCosmos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow! That was awesome! Could you please post the craft file? I love this thing!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry for the late reply! I put the craft file on kerbalsx.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Xendelaar/Xendelaar-TinyCopter\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/Xendelaar/Xendelaar-TinyCopter\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease note that it\u0027s a petty unbalanced craft and that it will start spinning if you reach high velocities.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDuplicating the seat and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003Ertg\u003C/abbr\u003E in radial placement would mitigate the balancing issue but would also increase the mass by 160kg. If you\u0027re not flying with mechjeb2 than I highly recommend doing this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you dont know what I mean, I made a video of a chopper that was really well balanced:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/Xx06tEC3CAs?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReplacing the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003Ertg\u003C/abbr\u003E with a solar panel would shave off an extra 50 kg or so.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidCosmos","CreatedById":192336,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-07T08:43:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223767200\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192900\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221586213342\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139535\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022xendelaar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, xendelaar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry for the late reply! I put the craft file on kerbalsx.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Xendelaar/Xendelaar-TinyCopter\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/Xendelaar/Xendelaar-TinyCopter\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease note that it\u0027s a petty unbalanced craft and that it will start spinning if you reach high velocities.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDuplicating the seat and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003Ertg\u003C/abbr\u003E in radial placement would mitigate the balancing issue but would also increase the mass by 160kg. If you\u0027re not flying with mechjeb2 than I highly recommend doing this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you dont know what I mean, I made a video of a chopper that was really well balanced:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/Xx06tEC3CAs?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReplacing the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003Ertg\u003C/abbr\u003E with a solar panel would shave off an extra 50 kg or so.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! Your piloting skills are really cool\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}